Euramax Holdings, Inc. Announces Acquisition of InvisaFlow




















June 02, 2016 16:00 ET

 | Source: OmniMax International, Inc.





NORCROSS, Ga., June  02, 2016  (GLOBE NEWSWIRE) -- Euramax Holdings, Inc., (“Euramax” or the “Company”), a leading supplier of metal and vinyl gutters and related components announced today that it has acquired the assets of InvisaFlow, LLC (“InvisaFlow”) an innovative manufacturer of water drainage products, including StealthSpout®, StealthFlow® and FlexGrate®.Richard C. Brown, President and CEO, commented, “We are very pleased to announce the acquisition of InvisaFlow, an innovative producer of solution oriented consumer products. InvisaFlow provides additional market penetration and complimentary products to our Amerimax Home Products brand, which is the leading manufacturer of rain-carrying systems in the US and Canada. This acquisition provides added market experience and product development capabilities which are core to our growth strategy. We are excited about the opportunities this acquisition provides to better serve our customers through a more diverse product portfolio and expanded product development opportunities.”About EuramaxEuramax is a global producer of architectural copper, metal cladding, patio, roof and lawn drainage, snow retention, windows and transportation products for original equipment manufacturers, distributors, contractors and home centers worldwide. Through a network of twelve brands, Euramax collectively offers more than 1,000 quality products to serve the diverse needs of its customers. Additional company brands include Alumawood, Amerimax Fabricated Products, Amerimax Windows & Doors, Berger Building Products, CopperCraft, Equinox Louvered Roof, Euramax Coated Products, Euramax Industries, Fabral, and Global Expanded Metals. Through strategic acquisitions and dedication to superior customer satisfaction, Euramax has become one of North America’s largest suppliers of building products. For more information, visit www.euramax.com.Contact 
Mary Cullin
Senior Vice President, Chief Financial Officer and Treasurer
Euramax Holdings, Inc.
303 Research Drive, Suite 400
Norcross, Georgia 30092
770-449-7066


